sequenceDiagram
    participant P as Player
    participant H as Hand
    participant C as Card
    participant OL as OrdersList
    participant D as Deck
    participant O as Order

    Note over P,O: Card Playing Sequence

    P->>H: playCard(index, player, ordersList, deck)
    H->>H: removeAt(index)
    H->>C: play(player, ordersList, deck)

    alt Card Type is Bomb
        C->>OL: add(new BombOrder())
    else Card Type is Reinforcement
        C->>OL: add(new DeployOrder())
    else Card Type is Blockade
        C->>OL: add(new BlockadeOrder())
    else Card Type is Airlift
        C->>OL: add(new AirliftOrder())
    else Card Type is Diplomacy
        C->>OL: add(new NegotiateOrder())
    end

    C->>D: returnCard(this)
    D->>D: cards.push_back(card)

    Note over P,O: Order Execution Sequence

    P->>OL: get(index)
    OL->>O: validate()

    alt Order is valid
        OL->>O: execute()
        O-->>P: Order executed
    else Order is invalid
        O-->>P: Order rejected
    end
